725903f-b.text:
150th Street, at the N.W. corner of One Hundred Fiftieth Ave., showing in a set of three views the J.C. Reimels farmhouse of 1913. James Francis was the owner in 1873, followed by his son, and then the present J.C. Mrs. Reimels had it in 1922 and William Dull in 1934. Another owner was B. Headerson from 1860 to 1873.
1922.
Views 1,2 and 3.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
